<HEADLINE>
<P>
MADAGASCAR SWAP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
I am almost certain to be the only one from Madagascar to live in Southern 
California. So when I saw the article Aug. 4 about the $1 million 
debt-for-nature swap, I decided to write. 
</P>
<P>
Thank you America. 
</P>
<P>
I know there must have been official thanks, but this is from a simple citizen 
who often feels sorry for his country. The idea is good. I thought of other 
ones: how about debt-for industrialization, debt-for education, debt-for 
transportation, debt-for-hygiene? 
</P>
<P>
Madagascar is a precious country, and not enough people know that. Madagascar 
needs help. That's why I came to study here. Thanks again. 
</P>
<P>
DOMINIQUE 
</P>
<P>
ANDRIAMANANTOA 
</P>
<P>
Huntington Beach 
</P>
</TEXT>
