<HEADLINE>
<P>
JAPANESE REPARATIONS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Editors at The Times have their priorities painfully confused. The editorial 
merely groused about the slow payment of dollars for Japanese reparations, yet 
The Times ignored the anniversary of V J Day, ending World War II, which cost 
so many American lives. Why didn't The Times honor them? 
</P>
<P>
M. JAFFE 
</P>
<P>
Thousand Oaks 
</P>
