<HEADLINE>
<P>
JAPANESE REPARATIONS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Enough is enough! Our government should keep its promise and immediately pay up 
and send a letter of apology to all Americans of Japanese extraction interned 
during World War II. They have suffered greatly, psychologically and 
financially. 
</P>
<P>
No other group of American citizens whose national extraction was that of our 
Axis enemies during World War II were subjected to the humiliation that our 
fellow Japanese-American citizens endured. 
</P>
<P>
Justice delayed is justice denied. Let's do the right thing now and work to put 
the shameful episode behind us. We are four U.S. veteran brothers who all 
served overseas (three in the Pacific battle zone) during World War II. 
</P>
<P>
EDMUND J. WIANECKI 
</P>
<P>
Venice 
</P>
<P>
STANLEY A. WIANECKI 
</P>
<P>
Venice 
</P>
<P>
EDWARD R. WIANECKI 
</P>
<P>
Los Angeles 
</P>
<P>
JOSEPH S. WIANECKI 
</P>
<P>
San Francisco 
