<P>
SOUTH BAY DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: SLAYING IS CITY'S 39TH HOMICIDE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 19-year-old Inglewood man was killed Monday night in what police say was a 
gang-related shooting. 
</P>
<P>
The death of Cozari Brown was the 39th killing in Inglewood this year, the 
highest number of homicides since 55 people died in the city in 1980, police 
said. A rise in gang violence is a major contributor to the increase in 
homicides, Sgt. Harold P. Moret said. 
</P>
<P>
Brown, who police said they believe was a gang member, was walking with a group 
of men at about 10 p.m. in the 10100 block of South Woodworth Avenue when a car 
pulled alongside. The car's occupants and the pedestrians exchanged words, and 
a passenger got out and opened fire on the group with a handgun, police said. 
The gunman got back in the car and the driver sped off, police said. 
</P>
<P>
Paramedics treated Brown at the scene. He later died at Daniel Freeman Memorial 
Hospital. 
</P>
</TEXT>
