<TEXT>
<P>
FIFA, world soccer's ruling body, rejected an appeal by Chile to let it host a 
World Cup qualifying match against Venezuela and ruled the match should be 
played in Mendoza, Argentina. 
</P>
<P>
Chile's soccer association appealed to FIFA on Tuesday to overturn its ban on 
the country playing host to the Venezuela match, and to allow the game to go 
ahead at a stadium other than Santiago's Estadio Nacional. 
</P>
<P>
FIFA imposed the suspension last Friday as one of a number of sanctions 
following disturbances at the Aug. 13 match between Chile and Brazil at the 
capital's stadium. 
