<TEXT>
<P>
The Kings' newly signed defenseman Larry Robinson, may sue the Montreal 
Canadiens for a retirement bonus he said was promised before he signed as a 
free agent. 
</P>
<P>
Robinson, 38, and his agent Don Cape said Canadien General Manager Serge Savard 
promised one year of full salary after his retirement but later placed on it a 
condition that he finish his NHL career in Montreal. 
</P>
<P>
Robinson turned down a one-year, $1-million offer, which included the bonus, 
from the Canadiens last month to accept the Kings' contract for two years plus 
an option year worth $1.5 million. 
