<HEADLINE>
<P>
ENCINO WINS, GETS REMATCH WITH SEOUL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
WASHINGTON, Pa. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Chris Ferebee struck out nine and Steve Chavez hit a two-run home run Wednesday 
as Encino defeated Orland Park, Ill., 7-3, to advance in the Pony League World 
Series. 
</P>
<P>
Encino must defeat Seoul tonight and again Friday to win the championship. 
Seoul defeated Encino, 4-0, Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
Chavez's third-inning home run scored Glen Carson and gave Encino a 3-2 lead. 
Orland Park, which committed seven errors, made three in the third, allowing 
two more runs to score. 
</P>
<P>
With his team trailing, 2-0, in the first, Encino's Justin Paperny singled to 
drive in Cesar Martinez, who had doubled. 
</P>
<P>
Orland Park scored a run in the fourth and Encino countered with two insurance 
runs in the sixth on Kevin Deitch's double and an RBI single by Jesus Perez. 
</P>
<P>
Although there is no official significance attached to the win, Encino Coach 
P.C. Shaw considers it tantamount to the national championship. 
</P>
<P>
"We don't get outclassed by anybody," Shaw said. "Check the record -- Encino 
just won the United States." 
</P>
</TEXT>
