<TEXT>
<P>
Arco Wins Oil Tanker Decision: A federal appellate court upheld the right of 
the U.S. Transportation Department to allow two oil tankers owned by Atlantic 
Richfield Co. to continue delivering Alaskan oil to the lower 48 states, Arco 
announced. The ruling by the U.S. Court of Appeals for the District of Columbia 
came in a lawsuit by independent tanker owners against the DOT challenging the 
use of tankers built with U.S. subsidies and intended for foreign service only. 
Such ships are normally barred from domestic service, but two Arco tankers were 
allowed to sail in the United States after Arco repaid about $87 million in 
subsidies used to build them. 
