ECHO PARK LIBRARY SITE TO BE DISCUSSED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A community meeting to discuss sites for the new Echo Park Library is scheduled 
for 2 p.m. Saturday at the library, 515 N. Levita Terrace. 
</P>
<P>
Members of the Friends of the Echo Park Library, the meeting's sponsor, want 
the new facility to be at a fire station soon to be vacated by the Los Angeles 
Fire Department, said spokeswoman Karen Jaeger. 
</P>
<P>
However, library officials are not considering the station at 534 E. Edgeware 
Road as a possible site. Jaeger said the meeting is being held in an attempt to 
find alternate sites for the building. 
</P>
<P>
