<HEADLINE>
<P>
SOLVENT TAKEN OFF DERAILED TRAIN; EVACUEES RETURN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From United Press International 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
TUCSON 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Hundreds of people evacuated near a derailed train were allowed to return home 
Wednesday after explosive naphtha solvent was unloaded from an overturned 
leaking tank car, authorities said. Nine cars of a 99-car Southern Pacific 
freight train jumped the tracks in the railroad yards on the southeastern edge 
of the city Tuesday. 
</P>
