</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The presidents of Brazil and Argentina agreed to dramatically increase trade 
between their countries and work together to solve their economic problems. 
"Unity is no longer a distant desire. . . . It is the means to end the vicious 
circle of dependence," Brazilian President Jose Sarney declared to his 
country's congress after signing an accord for bilateral integration on the 
second day of Argentine President Carlos Saul Menem's visit to Brasilia. The 
two leaders signed 15 documents to revitalize and increase trade between the 
nations. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
