<P>
Photo, Getting the Gain Without the Pain -- Sometimes it seems that everyone in 
the country is on a fitness binge. Parents and their 2- to 6-year-old children 
can even work out together in aerobic play classes at Live Oak Park offered by 
the Temple City Recreation Department. There are always some people who have a 
hard time getting started, so Brooke Graves, 2 1/2, gives her mother, Darla 
Davis, the push she needs. The class isn't all moving and sweating, though -- 
Dusty Wilf, 5, sits on her mother Lisa's lap during a story told by aerobics 
instructor Vikki Shore. The course is open to dads, but most of the parents 
present are of the mom variety. For some members of the class, all those moves 
are just too hard to figure out. This class has just ended, but a new class 
will begin Sept. 25. IRFAN KHAN / Los Angeles Times 
</P>
