<HEADLINE>
<P>
WEBER FUNERAL TODAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The funeral service for Jerry Weber, a prominent official of the Jewish 
community who was slain in a robbery at an automated teller machine, will be 
held today at 11 a.m. at the Valley Beth Shalom Synagogue, 15739 Ventura Blvd., 
Encino. 
</P>
<P>
Weber, 49, was the director of the Council on Jewish Life of the Jewish 
Federation Council of Greater Los Angeles for the last 10 years. He was shot 
and killed outside a bank in West Los Angeles early Tuesday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
