<P>
SCC'S ADAMS TAKES JOB WITH UC IRVINE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Doug Adams, who resigned as Southern California College baseball coach two 
weeks ago, has accepted a volunteer coaching position with the UC Irvine 
baseball team. 
</P>
<P>
"It's a great opportunity to coach at the Division I level without uprooting my 
family," Adams said. 
</P>
<P>
Adams, 38, was 30-21 last season at SCC, finishing second in the Golden State 
Athletic Conference. In his two years at SCC, Adams' record was 54-48. 
</P>
