<HEADLINE>
<P>
NIBBLES AND BITS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Scenes of Newport Beach by three local artists will be donated to the city by 
the Newport Beach Arts Commission Sept. 25 at 2 p.m. in the City Hall council 
chambers. A painting by John Cosby and watercolors by Scott Kennedy and Ruth 
Hynd (a former Newport Beach resident who now lives in Mendocino) will be added 
to other views of the city, which the commission has been collecting since the 
early 1970s. The presentation will launch the Newport Beach Salute to the Arts, 
Oct. 5 through 7. The public is invited. 
</P>
</TEXT>
