<P>
LORILLARD NAMES BULOVA'S TISCH CEO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
NEW YORK 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Lorillard Inc. announced today that Andrew H. Tisch has been named chairman and 
chief executive officer of the $1.8-billion tobacco firm. Tisch was most 
recently president of Bulova Corp., and will continue to be a director of the 
watch and defense products company. 
</P>
<P>
J. Robert Ave will remain with Lorillard as president. Ave has been with 
Lorillard 16 years and had been president and CEO since June, 1985. 
</P>
<P>
Lorillard Inc., a wholly owned subsidiary of Loews Corp., manufactures Kent, 
Kent III, Kent Golden Lights, Newport, Newport Stripes, Satin, True, Triumph, 
Max and Old Gold cigarettes. 
